                    <comment id="12357149" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 10 Nov 2005 07:06:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Proposed patch attached:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;insert(FieldDoc) keeps track of maxscore and calls super.insert(Object)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the maximum score is now kept track of, even if it is less than 1.0&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;getMaxScore() added&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This should also be slightly faster than the old way since there are only &quot;n&quot; comparisons against maxscore.&lt;br/&gt;
Previously, two comparisons would be done for every call to lessThan() (2*nlog&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/thumbs_down.gif&quot; height=&quot;19&quot; width=&quot;19&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; maybe?)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12357437" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sat, 12 Nov 2005 06:24:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
